  "key_conclusions": [
    "Donanemab significantly slowed clinical progression at 76 weeks in participants with early symptomatic Alzheimer disease and amyloid and tau pathology",
    "Greatest benefit observed in low/medium tau population (35.1% slowing)",
    "Combined population also showed significant benefit (22.3% slowing)",
    "High tau population showed no statistically significant benefit in primary outcome",
    "Donanemab demonstrated rapid amyloid clearance with 80.1% of participants achieving amyloid clearance (<24.1 Centiloids) at 76 weeks",
    "ARIA-E incidence was 24.0% with 6.1% symptomatic cases",
    "Treatment-related deaths were rare (0.35%)",
    "Indirect comparison shows lecanemab has significantly lower ARIA risk than donanemab"
